Description:
This sleek Christian Dior leather shoulder bag belonged to my mother when she bought it sometimes between 1976 and 78. A most perfect bag for someone blond like her!
Made out of sand colored leather, this smart bag offers two options: 
- One as a shoulder bag would look great with a skirt suit and boots for a retro look!

Product name: Antique Dollhouse, Amsterdam Warehouse, Exact model of real Amsterdam Architecture made in 1905 Collectible Dollhouse
Description:
Collectible Museum Piece, handmade warehouse classic Amsterdam building from the 1700's, the dollhouse, a boy's playhouse, is made in Amsterdam too in 1905.
This piece was made by a man for his son in 1905, he made it exactly according to the original building of which he was the owner his name can be seen on the house I.J. Heijland. The original building has unfortunately been replaced in the  1900's by a bigger building. It was a tobacco ware house in Amsterdam. It was made of solid wood making it heavy and firm, it is in excellent condition, especially considering its age of 111 years!
This will be an amazing conversation starter when people see this in your home or office!
It has a total height of 29 1/2'' (75 cm), it is 20'' (51 cm) wide and 13 1/2'' (34 cm) deep.
This is a great collectible antique piece.  I've never seen one like this before, what a great find. 
Please look at the pictures, so many details hard to explain. 
Would be an amazing collector's piece, wonderful gift for an architect, Amsterdam lover or just to make your home a bit more special!
Damages: A lot of paint work is chipped but that only adds extra charm, I cleaned it up but it will need a more thorough cleaning inside and you might want to apply some protection spray to prevent further peeling of paint. You can see that it had a door on the back but it mus have been removed soon afterwards as it clearly has not been there for many years. No repairs or alterations.

We’ve combined the classic baby shower gift of baby bedding with the relatively new concept of birth statistic announcements into one darling baby blanket. This modern baby blanket captures the sweetest moment of your life with the birth statistics, time, monogram, and name of your bouncing bundle of joy. Expertly printed onto exquisitely soft fleece, this baby blanket will offer you a unique way to announce your child to the world while also becoming a cherished childhood heirloom with time. Our baby blankets make the perfect baby shower gifts and are a favorite among new parents. 
We are passionate about creating one of a kind baby keepsake unique to your little one. I will work with you closely to custom design your blanket helping you every step of the way with choosing the perfect colors, fonts and graphics. Celebrating your new bundle of joy is a special moment and I will be thrilled to be part of it creating the perfect heirloom gift for you to cherish for years to come.

Materials: Our baby blankets are made of soft and snuggly premium fleece and are printed with high quality archival inks making them durable enough to stand the test of time.
BABY SWADDLING BLANKETS
These blankets are made of very soft and stretchy premium fleece perfect for swaddling your little bundle of joy. They are thin but keep your little one cozy and warm.
PLUSH (MINKY STYLE) BLANKETS
These blankets are made of heavy knit plush fleece and are often mistaken for cashmere blankets with the ultra soft feel and vibrant design. They are sure to withstand the test of time making them a beautiful keepsake gift to be cherished for years to come
Font Colors: Over 40 options and you may pick between 2 – 4 colors

Product name: Rustic Wedding Cake Stand, Fall Wedding, Wood Cake Stand, wood centerpiece, log cake stand, log slice, wood slice, rustic wedding decor
Description:
Rustic Wedding Cake Stand, Fall Wedding, Wood Cake Stand, wood centerpiece, log cake stand, log slice, wood slice, rustic wedding accessory, wood wedding
Made to order, select MINIMUM diameter. Woodburning available at additional cost as custom order. PURCHASE WOOD BURNING / CUSTOMIZATION SEPARATELY HERE: 
https://www.etsy.com/listing/484274529/custom-wood-burning-wood-burned-cake?ref=shop_home_active_1
Why you should by our log cake stands vs someone elses:
1. Ours our thicker than most and less likely to break. Thin slices are prone to breaking and cracking because they are cut across the grain. Plus our thicker slices just look better. We've had lots of customers come to us after their skinny slices have broken placing rush orders and expedited shipping.
2. We remove the bark, while many people like the look of the slices with bark they see on Pinterest etc..., hate to break this to you, but that is where many bugs live, in the bark and under the bark, spiders, beetles, all sorts of creepy crawlies. Plus the bark often just falls off or flakes off. We've had lots of customers come to us after their bark has fallen off placing rush orders and expedited shipping.
3. Our wood is dry, it's standing dead for many years, drying in the arid, low humidity, Colorado Rockies. It is not prone to mold or mildew as many woods are from wetter areas of the country.
4. Our wood is beautiful, and it goes very well with wedding cakes.
We suggest that you order a stand that is a bare minimum of 2" larger than your cakes diameter, which equates to a margin of just 1" all the way around. So if your cake is 12" you'll want to order a stand in the 14" - 15" range, or larger (with emphasis on the or larger). If your cake is 13", and you order a 14" - 15", you''ll be cutting it very close, with as little as 1/2" of margin. The size ranges mean that we're going to send you one somewhere in that range, we're not going to break down the sizes any finer than that, as these are trees and they vary a lot in shape and have wavy edges. Not trying to upsell, but check out our shop updates for some pictures that have been sent to us by customers who have ordered larger than needed and decorated on and around the stand. You can do some pretty creative things with a few inches of margin all the way around.
Also, keep in mind that the cake size you get from your baker might be the size of the cake pan, before frosting and decorations. And if your baker knows ahead of time what you're planning to put your cake on, they might want to coordinate and utilize the margin creatively. So talk to your baker, you might want to get them the stand while your planning your cake.
Also FYI, we get this question a fair bit, why is a 15" stand twice as much as a 10" stand? As the math works out the 15" stand is roughly twice the surface area, therefore, twice the wood, twice the work, twice the finish, it's like making two tens.
This is a log, a piece of an unprocessed natural tree, it has cracks, checks, knots, branches broken off, pieces splintered off, saw and tool marks from the harvesting process, and coloration and shapes will vary drastically from one tree to the next. If you are not okay with these natural variations then this product will not be right for you and we ask that you please refrain from ordering this. Please do read our shop policies, they are written to inform customers that might not be familiar with a natural product such as this as these variations might not be readily apparent from pictures in design magazines.
## Discount pricing available on purchase of ten or more, ask. ##
Since these are often being used for weddings we fulfill these on a first needed basis, we work to your schedule, we can turn them around with a week or two notice, but if you won't need it for a few months, then we put it on the calendar and get it to you with plenty of time to spare.

Product name: Wedding Tradition Pin-Something Old, Something New, Something Borrowed, Something Blue-Gift for the Bride, Swarovski Crystal Heart & Pearls
Description:
Something Old, Something New, Something Borrowed, Something Blue. This tradition comes from an Old English rhyme about the four objects that a bride adds to her wedding outfit or carries with her on the big day as good luck charms. They are little tokens of love that a mother,  sister, and/or maid honor will give the bride (or you can give them to yourself, too). Something old represents continuity; something new offers optimism for the future; something borrowed symbolizes borrowed happiness; something blue stands for purity, love, and fidelity. 
This pin can be attached to the inside of the bride's wedding gown, garter, or on her flower bouquet so she can carry the good luck charms with her on the wedding day. After the big day, the bride can choose to remove some or all of the charms the from the pin and wear them on the included Sterling silver chain as an everyday reminder of one of the most memorable and important days of her life.
What you get on your Wedding Tradition Pin:
1-Silver Plated Kilt Pin with 4 loops and lobster clasps
1-Cleaned & Polished Penny 25 years or older (something old)
1- Wire wrapped (24-Gauge) Sterling Silver Plated Peas in a Pod pendant that features two, white Swarovski crystal pearls representing the bride and groom (something new)
1-Silver-plated Stainless Steel place holder heart charm for the bride to take off and attach the 'something borrowed' (a small piece of jewelry or a special token from someone else that will be returned after the wedding)
1-Blue Swarovski crystal heart pendant (something blue)
1-24" Sterling Silver Rolo chain with a lobster clasp closure
*Each pin will be packaged in a sheer white gift pouch for you to present to the bride
I make all of my wedding pins by hand so please let me know if you have a customization request ahead of time and I will return your message in a timely matter so that we can design the perfect pin for your bride.
Upon purchase, you agree to the processing time (1-2 days) and have read my shipping policy. If you need this pin in a hurry, I can ship your order via USPS Priority Mail (2-3 day estimated delivery) or USPS Priority Express Mail which are both available at checkout. Once your order has shipped, you agree to track your order at USPS.com with the tracking number you will receive in an email upon (from Etsy). If you need to contact the USPS regarding delivery of your order, you may call them at 1-800-275-8777 or visit usps.com

Product name: Soft Copper Soldering Paste 1/2 oz Syringe, Eurotool Soldering Tools and Supplies
Description:
Soft Copper Soldering Paste 1/2 oz Syringe, Eurotool Soldering Tools and Supplies
Shipping includes Tracking and Insurance 
Although copper solder paste is not actually copper in color, it is less bright than silver solder paste and is also cadmium free. Flow point is 1325°F(718°C), melting point 1240°F(671°C). 1/2 ozt.  
HOW TO USE IT:
When soldering, make sure your metal is clean and dry. The heat is applied to the metal, not the solder itself. So all you do is put the soldering paste on the joint and heat the metal you're soldering, when the metal gets hot enough the solder will flow into the joint and seal it. When finished, dip it in the pickle solution if you have any discoloration or fire scale [this happens if the flame is really hot]. Remove from the pickle with fingers or copper tongs to avoid accidental contamination. I just use a small amount of warmed pickle for one type of metal and toss it when I'm finished soldering.
You can use a butane torch, soldering iron, alcohol lamp or even one of those butane lighters to heat the metal to get it hot enough for the solder to flow.
Contains Fluorides - use with adequate ventilation.
Note - Soldering doesn't 'fill holes' or empty spaces. For best results / stronger soldered joints, just make sure both sides of the metal you're joining fit flush before adding the paste :)

Get in the spirit with this "Roll Tide" University of Alabama necklace. The Roll Tide is a handcut brass or sterling silver pendant that is polished and sealed OR 14k gold plated and polished and sealed. The chain is a 14k gold filled sturdy chain or sterling silver chain (anti tarnish and allergy free)!
****Please choose necklace length and material - Brass or Gold Plated (GP) or Sterling Silver
Seen in picture with a 16 inch chain
****If you are not sure on the length of chain, please choose the shorter length you would like and then the "2 inches." • HOW IT'S MADE •
This is a handmade brass or sterling silver pendant polished and sealed OR plated with 14k gold and polished and sealed. The chain is a dainty 14k gold-filled chain (nickel free and anti-allergy) or a delicate sterling silver chain. I handsaw the letters out of brass or sterling silver sheet metal and then sand and polish the pendant. If you choose, it then goes through an electroplating process that bonds 14k gold to the brass pendant (all done by me in my studio). I finish up the piece by attaching it to a 14k gold-filled or sterling silver chain (anti-tarnish and allergy free).
If you choose brass as the material, it can tarnish over time (even though it is coated with renaissance wax). When that happens simply run the brass pendant portion under warm water and lightly scrub with a mild soap and soft toothbrush. Dry immediately when complete. Or see the following site: http://jewelrymakingjournal.com/how-to-clean-brass/
Gold plating is a method of depositing a thin layer of gold onto the surface of another metal by chemical or electrochemical plating.
Each necklace is handmade so please allow for variations
**The mining of most new precious metals, including silver, negatively impacts the environment and cultures surrounding mines. Precious metals can be recycled repeatedly with no degradation in quality, they are a naturally renewable resource - because of this, I use 100% recycled and re-refined metals, as well as recycled packaging. I do what I can to help minimize Ruth Ryan's effect on the environment and promote a healthier world.
